post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Once you replace the dealers and kingpins of the neighborhoods whose flashy lifestyle would look appealing to naive kids, drugs would lose some of their appeal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Right now \\(2019\\) children [as young as eight](https://www.channel5.com/show/8-years-old-and-smuggling-drugs/) are involved in the drug trade. This would not be allowed in a regulated market. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalising drugs would be damaging for public health. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug cartels will not cease their activities if drugs are legalised. They will simply move to other areas to keep their profits \\(drugs for children, black market drugs, human trafficking\\). So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The war on drugs has [cost civilian lives](https://www.vox.com/2014/10/29/7083371/swat-no-knock-raids-police-killed-civilians-dangerous-work-drugs). That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is not mutually exclusive with legalizing drugs. Both could be done. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This could lead individuals into a false sense of safety when it comes to drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Taking drugs can be a pleasurable experience.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A higher number of drugs users will create more work for the accident and emergency paramedic services that have to deal with people who have overdosed due to improper usage.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This isn't possible with the most popular date rape drug alcohol, at least not in higher doses, as it's taste is quite unmistakable."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is not fair to solve such a problem by prohibiting heroin use for everyone. It should be solved as a problem on its own. This could mean anything from forbidding heroin addicts to have children \\(or parents to use heroin\\), to forming organisations for helping such families. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The decision to use drugs should rest solely with individuals.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Economic hardship resulting from drug use would be better addressed by spending money on treatment, rather than attempting to control supply. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Taking drugs is not always a victimless crime, as drug users can harm others.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Constitutions can be amended by the Federal Government to suit their policies.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is no way to determine in advance what the additional resources/revenue will be used for by the government. It may not be earmarked for harm reduction. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is biased against those with mental illness. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A change in the law to deny all those who suffer self inflicted physical ill-health or mental trauma, including junkies, free access to the N.H.S., would, or at least should jolt the pleasure seekers out of their surreal world in which they enjoy a ''free ride''."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'They would have died on those drugs whether or not they were legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'They would have died on those drugs whether or not they were legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the US, as of 2018 there are roughly [235,000](https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2018.html) inmates behind bars for drug-related crimes. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Since drug addicts have an impaired sense of \\(rational\\) judgement, drug addiction is detrimental to personal autonomy.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, drug users could be less likely to leave dangerous paraphernalia \\(broken pipes, syringes, etc.\\) behind in public places as the fear of criminal penalties for the possession of drug paraphernalia would no longer be an issue. This would lessen risk of disease and injury. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Education including factual data will promote responsible and thoughtful use of drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs would save money used on police and agencies such as the DEA, as well as costs from all legal proceedings. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The additional tax revenue from drug commerce can be used to fund therapies and treatments. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal trade is already there. The legal trade would just drain their customer base. For criminal trade to survive in those conditions it would have to have either cheaper prices or better product. These are not easily achieved agains big corporations. At least the competition would seriously damage their overheads.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The first [anti-opium laws](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/brief-history-drug-war) in the 1870s were directed at Chinese immigrants. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Illegal drug producers and dealers use violence against police and competition. This just doesn't happen in legal businesses. The causes for this is also obvious. A legal business using violence will get fines and possibly be banned from participating in the legal market, and as such is a non-starter. I believe all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Opiates, such as heroin, are very detrimental to a persons health. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Shooting \\(illegally obtained\\) heroin is like playing Russian roulette every time: if a batch is too strong, over-dosing is likely. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Because pain is an important clinical symptom, legal recreational opioids may delay patients from seeking care in a timely fashion.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Without help some conditions could [worsen](https://deserthopetreatment.com/co-occurring-disorders/going-untreated/) to the point where they're a danger to others. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The risk of unknown purity and poor-quality drugs will be minimized. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the long run, the standing of the U.S. government did not suffer from ending the Alcohol Prohibition in the 1930s. Any potential reputational damage from ending marijuana or other prohibitions would be fleeting.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'One solution for recreational availability of such drugs could be to require that they emit an unmistakable coloring or odour/taste when dissolved in a drink.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Constitutions can be amended by the Federal Government to suit their policies.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help patients by facilitating access to medicines \\(drugs\\) that are currently hard to obtain. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many [deaths](http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-24581947) attributed to ecstasy \\(or MDMA\\) use are actually caused by other, unwanted ingredients.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Former inmates are significantly more at risk of drug-related mortality than the general population.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Inappropriate recreational drug use has negative health consequences. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition has been used as a racist policy to mass incarcerate people of color.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [war on drugs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_on_drugs) in the US was intended to be used as a tool to criminalise certain ethnic groups.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are often structurally similar legal compounds which can be researched instead of the illegal variation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Although education and information on the harmful side effects of [smoking](https://edition.cnn.com/2014/01/11/health/still-smoking/index.html) have been around for decades, millions of people still smoke.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Bettering education surrounding date rape and the drugs used for it would improve levels of prevention. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Drugs relate highly with](https://www.ojjdp.gov/pubs/coachesplaybook/effects_of_using.html) hampered physical and professional performance.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Most [drug users](http://theconversation.com/many-people-use-drugs-but-heres-why-most-dont-become-addicts-35504) can rely on supportive networks and loving families. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government would be giving up authority to empower the individual. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Education on how to be safe with drugs can be seen as an incentive to use them. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is possible that decriminalization dissuades those who specifically start using drugs as a way of breaking the law, such as [early data from Portugal](https://www.leafly.com/news/politics/portugal-drug-decriminalization-statistics) suggests. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The increased tax revenue could enable increased government spending, which [results in more jobs](https://www.americanprogress.org/issues/economy/reports/2011/09/08/10257/government-spending-can-create-jobs-and-it-has/).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The additional tax revenue from drug commerce can be used to fund therapies and treatments. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It is unlikely that a low level drug dealer will shift to trafficking human beings the moment drugs get legalised. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Education and information might not be enough to ensure thoughtful drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "[Ricin](https://emergency.cdc.gov/agent/ricin/facts.asp), a highly poisonous substance, is created from castor beans. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The [global financial crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Financial_crisis_of_2007%E2%80%932008) was caused by big companies acting with only their profits in mind, and the detrimental effects are still felt today. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Regulations that prohibit working under the influence of alcohol can trivially be expanded to include all drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [majority](http://www.independent.co.uk/news/habits-most-drug-users-are-happy-successful-people-with-a-taste-for-the-good-life-1292155.html) of young individuals consuming illegal substances lead fulfilling and successful lives.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Latin American [\\(Mexican](https://scholar.harvard.edu/vrios/publications/role-drug-related-violence-and-extortion-promoting-mexican-migration)\\) asylum seeking will decrease. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Personal autonomy](https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/personal_autonomy) is not a fundamental right in the US constitution.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs being illegal prevented addiction, there would be no drug addicted person. Thus, there is no prevention by just keeping drugs illegal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poor people use drugs as a temporary escape from poverty [\\(Scottish Drugs Forum, p. 12\\)](http://www.dldocs.stir.ac.uk/documents/drugpovertylitrev.pdf). Criminalization of this behavior does not help them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Research chemicals, which are used as [date rape drugs](https://drugabuse.com/date-rape-drugs/), are constantly evolving and changing formulations to escape existing regulation. It is unlikely that the law would be able to control all of them. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is [no/little research](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/drugfacts/hallucinogens) regarding the long-term effects of hallucinogens. So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Coming from families with unstable backgrounds alone is associated with withdrawal from societal life. It might be the cause of both the withdrawal and the drug use. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Sensible legal drug policy would uses taxes to keep prices equal or slightly below current black market prices to keep that from occuring. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs relate frequently with [suicide attempts](https://www.encyclopedia.com/education/encyclopedias-almanacs-transcripts-and-maps/accidents-and-injuries-drugs). So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'They may lose their job and thus stop contributing to society and paying taxes.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It is likely that a small group who are motivated not to take hard drugs solely because they are illegal would then try drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The use of psychoactive substances](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3202501/) has been a part of human culture for thousands of years; drugs have been used for religious, medical or recreational purposes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is only true in the case of people whose drug use either causes them to become dangerous or interferes with their lives. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has criminalized a large number of otherwise innocent individuals.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is better to educate people on how to use valuable-yet-dangerous things safely than to ban their use entirely.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Having the option to buy regulated drugs is surely better than only having the black market option. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Currently, in many countries, stores which sell age-restricted products such as alcohol have strict regulations in place to ensure the consumer is of appropriate age. The same could be done with other drugs. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization might lead to increased consumption among children.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Allowing people to become addicted merely so we can understand addiction is socially and medically irresponsible. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This limits what we know about these compounds as well as to what length we are able to develop treatments for those struggling with addiction \\(physical and mental\\) as well as treatment for acute toxicity.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Although social prejudice may remain, addicts could seek help far easier if there were no fear of legal repercussions.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People would prefer less addicting drugs, so as to lessen the risk of taking them. This would lead to companies to develop less addictive drugs as well.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "They already do this with alcohol or cigarettes, which hasn't caused our society to collapse."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Children of addicts may be raised in an environment which makes it [likelier for them](https://www.samhsa.gov/data/sites/default/files/report_3223/ShortReport-3223.html) to consume and become addicts in the future.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "A parent's drugs addiction can cause a child to suffer emotional harm and a lack of future stability as it can reduce the parent's life expectancy, causing them to die young. So drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The increased tax revenue could enable increased government spending, which [results in more jobs](https://www.americanprogress.org/issues/economy/reports/2011/09/08/10257/government-spending-can-create-jobs-and-it-has/).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "But we don't make moral judgements all the time every day. We all need to stop thinking clearly and rationally every now and then, for activities including but not limited to play, fun, pleasure, love, chilling out, taking a load off… So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [majority](http://www.independent.co.uk/news/habits-most-drug-users-are-happy-successful-people-with-a-taste-for-the-good-life-1292155.html) of young individuals consuming illegal substances lead fulfilling and successful lives.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [2018 poll](https://sputniknews.com/analysis/201809141068019139-uk-drugs-policy-children-threat/) reported that children find it easier to acquire illegal substances than legal ones.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Several 'great' artists have died from an overdose on drugs and thus actually causing negative contributions to human culture as the world is deprived of their 'artwork'."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When drugs are legal, health institutions can give people valuable information on how much you can take and other health advice on drugs. Now they can't because they would 'support' taking drugs and so also 'support' something illegal. I believe all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing would lead to a better understanding of addiction in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Nearly all negative effects of addicts on their families are not fueled by the addiction itself, but the fact that the drug they are addicted to is made illegal by the ban on drugs. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the US, as of 2018 there are roughly [235,000](https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2018.html) inmates behind bars for drug-related crimes. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A large portion of the public is irresponsible. Giving everyone the opportunity to use \\(or abuse\\) drugs would have negative consequences on these individuals.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Taking drugs is not always a victimless crime, as drug users can harm others.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Justifying a ban because it provides people with more autonomy is an inherent contradiction. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'When obtaining drugs legally people can be sure that the drugs are pure and accurately measured. With the illegal drug market drugs are often mis-sold, inaccurately measured or cut with other substances.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "As long as the taxes don't surpass the higher costs of the black market businesses, there is no reason to believe that legal drugs would be more expensive. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
